Because it is against the law to abort in the country any time other than to save the life of the woman, there is a great need for objective sources of information from which we, as a Commission, can inform our Recommendation 9-4.
In future work, we can go further, adding Opportunities A and B from Recommendation 9-2 to understand how men and boys contribute to healthy sexual and reproductive lives for all people.
The Equal Participation Cluster should consider creating a gender sensitive advocacy working group. Please feel free to reach out to Shazia for additional information about fostering the voices of the Silence Breakers, and for more information about our gender advocacy related work.
The Governance and Legal Cluster should review its work on human rights to ensure the import of multiple cultures and beliefs, cultural relativism, human dignity, traditional values, religious beliefs, and moral beliefs.
